  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2023-06-14",
    "date": "2023-10-18T17:44:06Z",
    "text": "Expanded Food Safety Investigation Act of 2023\n\nThis bill provides that the Food and Drug Administration (FDA) may, under specified circumstances,\u00a0request access to a concentrated animal-feeding operation (i.e., a stabled or confined animal-feeding operation) to conduct microbial sampling.\n\nSpecifically, the bill allows the FDA to request access if the FDA determines that sampling is necessary to facilitate an investigation of a foodborne-illness outbreak, determine the cause of the outbreak, or address other public health needs.\n\nThe bill provides that such an operation shall be subject to penalties for refusing such a sampling."
  },
